│ The `simplifySRemInst` function simplifies the `srem` instruction. It already includes some handling for specific cases, such as when the divisor is zero or when the operands are negated. However, it does not  │
│ explicitly check for the undefined behavior of division by zero in all cases.                                                                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ To address the issue, we can add a check at the beginning of the function to ensure that the divisor (`Op1`) is not zero. If it is zero, we can return `PoisonValue` to indicate undefined behavior. This will    │
│ prevent further propagation of undefined behavior during optimization.                                                                                                                                            │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ I will now proceed to implement this fix.                                                                                                                                                                         │
